      <article>
        <h3>Semantic Structure</h3>
        <p>Using semantic HTML elements such as <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;main&gt;</code>, and <code>&lt;footer&gt;</code> makes your content easier to understand for both users and search engines.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>Accessibility</h3>
        <p>Accessibility features, such as ARIA roles and proper heading structure, help users who rely on screen readers navigate the site more efficiently.</p>
      </article>

      <article>
        <h3>SEO Best Practices</h3>
        <p>Incorporating clear titles, meta descriptions, and keyword-rich headings improves your page's discoverability by search engines.</p>
